<subSubSection box="[151,545,1401,1427]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,545,1401,1427]" box="[151,545,1401,1427]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,545,1401,1427]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,545,1401,1427]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[238,545,1401,1427]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Mylabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,346,1401,1427]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Mylabris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius" box="[353,545,1401,1427]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1775) Systema entomologicae, systen insectorum classes, ordines, genera, species, adiectis synonymis, locis, descriptionibus, observationibus. Libraria Kortii, Flensburgi / Lipsiae, [32] + 832 pp." type="book" year="1775">
Fabricius, 
<number box="[486,545,1401,1427]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1775.0">1775</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1466,2031]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,307,1466,1491]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<typeStatus box="[151,210,1466,1491]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Type</typeStatus>
species.
</emphasis>
The definition of the 
<typeStatus box="[556,604,1467,1491]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
species of this genus, and consequently of the nominate subgenus, is still being debated. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Selander" box="[486,669,1502,1527]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Selander, R. B. (1991) On the Nomenclature and Classification of the Meloidae (Coleoptera). Insecta Mundi, 5, 65 - 94." type="journal article" year="1991">
Selander (
<number box="[603,661,1503,1527]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and other authors, the 
<typeStatus box="[940,988,1503,1527]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus is 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Meloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cichorii">
<emphasis box="[1269,1436,1502,1527]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Meloe cichorii</emphasis>
Linnaeus, 
<number box="[268,327,1538,1563]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1758.0">1758</number>
</taxonomicName>
, by subsequent designation (
<bibRefCitation author="Latreille" box="[648,876,1538,1563]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Latreille, P. A. (1810) Considerations generales sur l'ordre naturel des animaux composant les classes des crustaces, des arachnides, et des insectes; avec un tableau methodique de leurs genres, dispses en familles. F. Schoell, Paris, 444 pp." type="book" year="1810">
Latreille, 
<number box="[758,818,1539,1563]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1810.0">1810</number>
: 
<number box="[829,876,1539,1563]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="430.0">430</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). However, in the present paper we agree with the considerations published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna" box="[473,742,1574,1599]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Bologna, M. A. &amp; Pinto, J. D. (2002) The Old World genera of Meloidae (Coleoptera): a key and synopsis. Journal of Natural History, 36, 2013 - 2102. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930110062318" type="journal article" year="2002">
Bologna &amp; Pinto (
<number box="[680,742,1575,1599]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[752,810,1574,1599]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2066.0">2066</number>
) (see also Bologna, 
<number box="[1040,1101,1575,1599]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2008.0">2008</number>
). The fact that 
<taxonomicName box="[1271,1436,1574,1599]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Meloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cichorii">
<emphasis box="[1271,1436,1574,1599]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Meloe cichorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the 
<typeStatus box="[224,272,1611,1635]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[407,508,1610,1635]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Mylabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[407,508,1610,1635]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Mylabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is problematic. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kuzin" box="[698,851,1610,1635]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Kuzin, V. S. (1954) K poznanyyu systemy narybnikov (Coleoptera, Meloidae, Mylabrini). Trudy Vsesoyznogo Entomologicheskogo Obshchestva, 44, 336 - 379." type="journal article" year="1954">
Kuzin (
<number box="[784,842,1610,1635]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1954.0">1954</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
ignored the Latreilleâ€™s designation and transferred 
<taxonomicName box="[151,238,1646,1671]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Meloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cichorii">
<emphasis box="[151,238,1646,1671]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">cichorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName box="[278,368,1646,1671]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[278,368,1646,1671]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Hycleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[as 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[419,520,1646,1671]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Mylabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[419,520,1646,1671]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Mylabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[539,667,1646,1671]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Euzonabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[539,667,1646,1671]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Euzonabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[858,948,1646,1671]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[858,948,1646,1671]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Hycleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
]; its placement has been adopted by other workers (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna" box="[329,522,1682,1707]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Bologna, M. A. (1991 a) Coleoptera Meloidae. Fauna d'Italia. XXVIII. Calderini, Bologna, xiv + 541 pp." type="book" year="1991" yearSuffix="a">
Bologna, 
<number box="[450,509,1683,1707]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1991.0">1991</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[545,592,1683,1707]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="207.0">207</number>
). Following Kuzinâ€™s definition of 
<taxonomicName box="[1032,1118,1682,1707]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Meloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cichorii">
<emphasis box="[1032,1118,1682,1707]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">cichorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, will result in extensive nomenclatural disruption in these two most speciose genera of Mylabrini. However, a recent examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[151,199,1755,1779]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName box="[312,477,1754,1779]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Meloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cichorii">
<emphasis box="[312,477,1754,1779]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Meloe cichorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode box="[493,577,1755,1779]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/80z8-1h9s" name="Uppsala University, Zoological Museum" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">UUZM</collectionCode>
and the beetle collection of the Linnean Society of London) shows that 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Meloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cichorii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">M. cichorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mixed and includes not only 
<taxonomicName box="[599,784,1790,1815]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cichorii">
<emphasis box="[599,784,1790,1815]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Hycleus cichorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as defined by recent authors, but also 
<taxonomicName authority="Pallas" authorityName="Pallas" authorityYear="1775" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Mylabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[1220,1436,1790,1815]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Mylabris variabilis</emphasis>
(Pallas)
</taxonomicName>
and other mylabrine species belonging to different genera. Consequently there are two options for preserving current generic definitions: (a) Designation of the representative of 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[1096,1247,1862,1887]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Mylabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[1096,1247,1862,1887]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">M. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<typeStatus box="[1297,1400,1862,1887]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[151,352,1898,1923]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Mylabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cichorii">
<emphasis box="[151,352,1898,1923]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Mylabris cichorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; or (b) petition the International Commission of Zoological Nomenclature to set aside the designation of 
<taxonomicName box="[317,481,1934,1959]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Meloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cichorii">
<emphasis box="[317,481,1934,1959]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Meloe cichorii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<typeStatus box="[517,565,1935,1959]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
species and accept the designation of 
<taxonomicName authority="Linne. The" authorityName="Linne. The" box="[993,1372,1934,1959]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Meloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadripunctata">
<emphasis box="[993,1242,1934,1959]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Meloe quadripunctata</emphasis>
LinnÃ©. The
</taxonomicName>
latter was inappropriately designated the 
<typeStatus box="[555,603,1971,1995]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">type</typeStatus>
species by 
<bibRefCitation box="[738,998,1970,1995]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Pardo Alcaide, A. (1954 a) Estudios sobre Meloidae IV. Sobre algunos Mylabris Fabr. del Norteafricano. Eos, Revista Espanola de Entomologia, 30, 331 - 344." type="journal article">
Pardo Alcaide (
<number box="[917,977,1970,1995]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1954.0">1954</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
, but is in accordance with the modern definition of 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[297,398,2006,2031]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Mylabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[297,398,2006,2031]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Mylabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kuzin" box="[413,556,2006,2031]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Kuzin, V. S. (1954) K poznanyyu systemy narybnikov (Coleoptera, Meloidae, Mylabrini). Trudy Vsesoyznogo Entomologicheskogo Obshchestva, 44, 336 - 379." type="journal article" year="1954">
Kuzin, 
<number box="[497,556,2006,2031]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1954.0">1954</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna" box="[568,749,2006,2031]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Bologna, M. A. (1991 a) Coleoptera Meloidae. Fauna d'Italia. XXVIII. Calderini, Bologna, xiv + 541 pp." type="book" year="1991" yearSuffix="a">
Bologna, 
<number box="[677,736,2007,2031]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1991.0">1991</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
